HEADWORD: Podophyllous
<hw>Pod`o*phyl"lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having thin, flat, leaflike locomotive
organs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or composing, the
layer of tissue, made up of lamin⟦ae⟧, beneath a horse's hoof.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Podophyllum</ent>⟦br⟧
